<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-02-08T10:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-02-08T10:41:00-05:00" n="307" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">856d.6363/507: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">The
                                        Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-02-08T16:00:00+00:19"><hi rend="italic">February 8,
                                        1928—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received February 8—12:50
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>7. My telegram No. 6, February 4, 5 p.m. Am gratified to report Koloniale
                            oil bill approved this afternoon by the first chamber without record
                            vote.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi></signed></closer>
